[09:00.18]	Five summers have I spent in furthest Greece,
[09:04.19]	Roaming clean through the bounds of Asia,
[09:07.88]	And, coasting homeward, came to Ephesus;
[09:11.34]	Hopeless to find, yet loath to leave unsought
[09:15.34]	Or that or any place that harbours men.
[09:18.87]	But here must end the story of my life;
[09:22.41]	And happy were I in my timely death,
[09:25.71]	Could all my travels warrant me they live.
[09:29.48]DUKE SOLINUS	Hapless AEgeon, whom the fates have mark'd
[09:33.25]	To bear the extremity of dire mishap!
[09:36.62]	Now, trust me, were it not against our laws,
[09:40.39]	Against my crown, my oath, my dignity,
[09:43.69]	Which princes, would they, may not disannul,
